file=Brand Studio/tempo/custom/sound-identity/assets/sonic-guide-template.md · [ns:[Brand Name] Sonic Guide — TEMPLATE=> Operator-approved, versioned, one per brand at tempo's config `sonic_guide_path`.\n> Derived from the brand kit's mood (atlas), voice register (lena), and arc range (weave) —\n> sound never contradicts the other definers. Rules written as testable statements.\n\n**Brand:** [name] \· **Version:** [v1.0] \· **Approved:** [date] \· **Derived from:** [kit vX, voice guide vY, arc vZ]\n · 1mm:1. Music mood ranges (testable)=- **Default range:** [e.g., "warm acoustic, mid-tempo; energetic but never frantic"]\n- **Per content type:** [chapters/promos/tutorials — ranges per type]\n- **Never:** [e.g., "EDM drops, cinematic trailer bombast, stock 'corporate uplifting'"]\n · 2vt:2. VO tone=[Register consistent with lena's guide — e.g., "warm, unhurried, first-person; no announcer voice, no vocal fry-bait." Approved voices/artists if any.]\n · 3sl:3. Sonic logo / signature (if any)=[Intro/outro sounds, their files, usage rules — or "none yet."]\n · tb=\| Track \| Why it's on-sound \| Registry ref \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| Date \| v \| Change \| Approved by \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|